NBA ALL-STAR WEEKEND
February 12, 2010
Carmelo Anthony
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q. (On the Boston Celtics:)  
 CARMELO ANTHONY: I think as a basketball city Boston was always very underrated. We've got some of the best players that ever played the game come out of there, Sam Cassell, Reggie Lewis, Reggie Williams, David Wingate, the list goes on and on and on. We are underrated as a city. We are respected, we're just underrated.  
  
  Q. Who would you say is the best player out of Baltimore (Inaudible).   
 CARMELO ANTHONY: Out of Baltimore? Skip Wise.   
  
  Q. Who is the toughest player on your team?   
 CARMELO ANTHONY: I don't know, man, everybody has their nights. I don't know, I can't just pick one person and say that they're the toughest player.   
  
  Q. How would you grade yourself?  
 CARMELO ANTHONY: How would I grade myself? I wouldn't.   
  
  Q. If you were a super hero, which one would you be?  
 CARMELO ANTHONY: Batman.  
  
  Q. Why?  
 CARMELO ANTHONY: Tough, tenacious, goes and takes care of business how he wants to take care of it, let him do it his way.   
   
  End of FastScripts  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT